## How Multi-Page Versions Work

For a multi-page artifact, the version belongs to the **set**, not just one file.

When any page changes materially, update the set version here and create a frozen snapshot for the new baseline.

## Switching The Current Version

To make an older version current again:

1. Confirm which old version should become current.
2. Restore the whole artifact set from the same commit or frozen snapshot.
3. Update this register with the new current version and rationale.
4. Validate wiki navigation and snapshot membership.
5. Commit the restored set to `Wave.wiki`.

Do not restore only one page from an old baseline unless this register explains the mixed-version exception.
